This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves a linguistic analysis of scientific manuscripts. It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it analyses the peer review process of AI conferences and uses AI-related jargon. Additionally, it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it analyses the word content related to machine learning and neural networks. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it analyses the references included in the manuscripts. Finally, it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses biases in the peer review process.
